Package: normet
Type: Package
Title: Normalisation, Decomposition, and Counterfactual Modelling for Air Quality Time-series
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Congbo", "Song", email = "congbo.song@manchester.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7948-4834"))
Maintainer: Congbo Song <congbo.song@manchester.ac.uk>
Description: Provides a suite of tools for advanced air quality time series analysis.
    Core functionalities include meteorological normalisation (de-weathering)
    to reveal underlying trends in data like air pollution concentrations,
    and causal inference using both classic and machine learning-based
    Synthetic Control Methods (SCM). The package features high-level workflows
    for uncertainty quantification, time-series decomposition, and robust
    placebo tests, powered by H2O AutoML or lightgbm backends.
